  "footnotes": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "text": "You must follow these requirements if you entered MIT in Fall 2024 or later."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "text": "Includes subjects as of Fall 2026"
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "text": "Each completed subject can only be used to satisfy at most one _required_ subject but can be used to satisfy multiple _additional constraints_."
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "text": "![](https://eecsis.mit.edu/images/fall.gif): only offered fall term ![](https://eecsis.mit.edu/images/spring.gif): only offered spring term grey: not offered this academic year."
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "text": "The prerequisites for 6.1210 can be satisfied in two different ways:"
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "text": "take 6.100A (6 units) and 6.1200 (12 units), or"
    },
    {
      "id": "7",
      "text": "take 6.100A (6 units) and 6.120A (6 units) and one of the following probability courses: 6.3700, 6.3800, 18.05, or 18.600 (all 12 units). You can petition to use the required probability course as one of the two restricted electives, provided that the second restricted elective is from Course 7."
    }
  ],
